context: The Procession, held at <a0_0>sundown<a0_0/>, consists of a <a4_0>non-motorized<a4_0/> parade through downtown Tucson featuring many floats, sculptures, and memorials, in which the community is encouraged to participate. The parade is followed by performances on an outdoor stage, culminating in the burning of <a1_0>an urn in which written prayers have been collected from participants and spectators<a1_0/>. The event is organized and funded by the <a3_0>non-profit arts organization<a3_0/> <a2_0>Many Mouths One Stomach<a2_0/>, with the assistance of many volunteers and donations from the public and local businesses.
